        "timestamp": "2020-01-13 21:30:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nI guess the cross-product of the lists, project-name x stream x job, is formed here?  I.e., for each project-name, for all branches, for each job create a Jenkins config?  When you restrict branch within a job, what happens? Do you get multiple jobs that have different names but behind the scenes use the same branch?",
